x4codes.hlp: Brookhaven National Laboratory, Upton, NY, United States of America
Brookhaven National Laboratory, Upton, NY, United States of America

x4freetext: First, between resonances method was applied
below 1 keV. From known resonance parameters, sigma
res, was calculated as function of energy. Second,
average-cross-section method was applied in the keV
region. The average cross section was observed, which
depends on the average properties of the nuclei, such
as strength function. The transmission vs flight-time
curve averaged over resonances has a slope that for
thin samples is proportional to the strength functions.
